VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'conventional radios. Of course, it\'s completely private and no, China, Bofang, or anyone else isn\'t interested in listening to you chat to your cronies on them. The last point, of course, is the price. Just over £60 on Bangod for'

[06:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'two radios, two SIMs, and two data plans, which Bofang renew for free in 3 years. Now, there is a couple of disadvantages. You are reliant on the cellular networks. But if you buy this'

[06:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'package knowing what it is and its limitations, this really isn\'t a disadvantage. Depending on what networks are live in your area and what coverage you have, there may be some latency. Mine appear to be on O2 and where I am,'

[06:47] [scene:talk]
